			<div id="post-18" class="post-18 post type-post hentry category-gardening">
			<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://www.redbudfarms.com/the-real-importance-of-gardening/" title="Permalink to The Real Importance of Gardening" rel="bookmark">The Real Importance of Gardening</a></h2>

			<div class="entry-meta">
				<span class="meta-prep meta-prep-author">Posted on</span> <a href="http://www.redbudfarms.com/the-real-importance-of-gardening/" title="8:25 pm" rel="bookmark"><span class="entry-date">January 25, 2011</span></a> <span class="meta-sep">by</span> <span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="http://www.redbudfarms.com/author/firstpage/" title="View all posts by Barley">Barley</a></span>			</div><!-- .entry-meta -->

				<div class="entry-content">
				<p>Are you having plan to make your own garden? Gardening is certainly a wonderful hobby. Some people focus merely on growing flowers and plants, while others grow vegetables. Some gardeners are so aggravated and take pleasure in gardening so much that they grow everything, from flowers to vegetables.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.redbudfarms.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/gardening.jpg"><img class="alignright size-medium wp-image-20" src="http://www.redbudfarms.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/gardening-245x300.jpg" alt="" width="245" height="300" /></a>Back in the elderly days, individuals had to live off whatever food they grew in their garden. These people were typically very conservative with the way they handled their gardening. They would harvest their food at the same time, in the fall of each year. After harvesting, they would can a lot of vegetables such as: corn, tomatoes, beans and many other vegetables. This was what they would consume during the winter, and even into the next gardening season. This was a way of life for people during this time. Even though the people back then were unfortunate and were forced to grow their own food, they were healthier. They lived longer than us do now, and their quality of life was also better. Another thing that was better back then was the content of the soil. The soil was a whole lot richer in vitamins and nutrients than it is at this time.</p>
<p>Store-bought fruits and vegetables are so unhealthful, with all pesticides that were used while growing it. They may look and go through the same, but they aren&#8217;t the same, and the nutrient-depleted soil doesn&#8217;t make things better, simply worse. It is very helpful if you do grow your own food. In this manner, you are sure that the whole food that you eat is all safe without pesticides on it. Now, if you are hesitant in making a garden, I am going to share to you some hints on how to make a garden.</p>
<p>-The kind of soil. You have to make sure that the soil content is high. Make certain that the soil is good for vegetables, flowers and crops.</p>
<p>-Size. – This factor is very vital to make out in order for you to know how many crops or flowers you can plant on it.</p>
<p>-Budget. &#8211; It is very necessary for you to distinguish your budget in order for you to limit the extra expenses in making your garden.</p>
							</div><!-- .entry-content -->
	
